nixos-microsegebpf is licensed primarily under the MIT License, with
the kernel-side eBPF C source dual-licensed MIT/GPL-2.0 as required
by the Linux BPF subsystem to use GPL-only kernel helpers.

Per-file licensing follows the SPDX / REUSE convention:

  * Userspace code (Go, Nix, docs)
      SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
      Full text: LICENSES/MIT.txt

  * Kernel-side eBPF source (bpf/microseg.c)
      SPDX-License-Identifier: (MIT AND GPL-2.0-only)
      Runtime LICENSE string: "Dual MIT/GPL"
      Full texts: LICENSES/MIT.txt, available at
        https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/gpl-2.0.txt

  * Generated BPF artefacts (bpf/vmlinux.h, bpf/microseg_bpfel.{go,o})
      SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0-only
      Derived from the running kernel's BTF; carry the kernel's
      license. See REUSE.toml for the per-path declaration.

  * Documentation (README*.md, ARCHITECTURE*.md)
      Inline SPDX header in each file.

REUSE compliance: every file in this repository has either an
in-file `SPDX-License-Identifier:` header or a path glob in
`REUSE.toml`. Run `reuse lint` to verify.

The complete MIT text is in `LICENSES/MIT.txt`.
